Police acting on a tip off nabbed 15 high school students who were found drinking alcohol at Nkubu township.   The students were arrested at different pubs in Imenti South sub county on Monday.  Imenti South police boss William Maronga said officers who had been tipped off by members of the public arrested the learners alongside three other people.  “We found eight students in one of the clubs drinking beer,” said Maronga.  A waiter at the bar was also arrested for selling alcohol to the minors.  High-end clubs lose bid to reopen doors   Joho: Nightclubs in Mombasa to be closed for 30 days  Shock as Lionel Messi narrowly escapes attack while on holiday  Eight Athletes injured in nightclub balcony collapse at world swim meet The police chief said the students who were not in school uniform at the time of arrest, disclosed that they were students from different institutions.  Raided another club  “At around 9pm we raided another club and found another group of seven students drinking alcohol. We arrested them alongside the waiter and the person who was serving the alcohol. All were boys and under 18 years ,” Maronga said.  At the same time, the police boss has warned students against visiting such establishments and bar operators against serving alcohol to minors, saying appropriate deterrence measures will be taken against them.  He said it's up to the court to take whatever the action it deemed fit against the offenders.  “The Government will take action against bar owners who allow minors into their premises, and serve them alcohol,” he said.   Death toll in the Florida nightclub shooting surpasses 50.  Popular night club in Rongai brought down by fire  Popular night club in Rongai brought down by fire By Jane Mugambi | 2 hours ago By Jane Mugambi | 11 hours ago By Fidelis Kabunyi | 11 hours ago By Stevens Muendo | 16 hours ago